---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Sustainability Guide - Irish Garden Assistant">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Irish Gardening Sustainability Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      A comprehensive guide to sustainable gardening practices tailored for Irish gardens, climate, and ecosystems.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
      <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
          <div class="rounded-full bg-primary/20 p-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-primary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3.055 11H5a2 2 0 012 2v1a2 2 0 002 2 2 2 0 012 2v2.945M8 3.935V5.5A2.5 2.5 0 0010.5 8h.5a2 2 0 012 2 2 2 0 104 0 2 2 0 012-2h1.064M15 20.488V18a2 2 0 012-2h3.064M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Environmental Benefits</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-sm mb-4">Discover how sustainable gardening helps protect Ireland's unique ecosystems</p>
        <a href="#environmental" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
          <div class="rounded-full bg-secondary/20 p-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-secondary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Seasonal Practices</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-sm mb-4">Month-by-month guide to sustainable gardening in Ireland's climate</p>
        <a href="#seasonal" class="btn btn-secondary btn-block">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
          <div class="rounded-full bg-accent/20 p-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-3 7h3m-3 4h3m-6-4h.01M9 16h.01" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Practical Steps</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-sm mb-4">Simple actions you can take today to make your garden more sustainable</p>
        <a href="#practical" class="btn btn-accent btn-block">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Environmental Benefits Section -->
    <section id="environmental" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 border-b pb-2">Environmental Benefits of Sustainable Gardening in Ireland</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Protecting Irish Biodiversity</h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Ireland's biodiversity faces significant challenges, with many native species in decline. 
            Sustainable gardening creates havens for wildlife, supporting pollinators like the 
            endangered Great Yellow Bumblebee and native butterflies.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            By planting native species such as hawthorn, rowan, and bird cherry, you provide 
            essential food and habitat for Ireland's wildlife. Native wildflowers like foxgloves, 
            primroses, and wild strawberries support specific insect species that have evolved 
            alongside them.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Did You Know?</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">
              Ireland is home to over 100 bee species, but one-third are threatened with extinction. 
              Gardens can serve as crucial corridors between fragmented natural habitats.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Carbon Storage and Climate Resilience</h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Irish gardens collectively cover a significant land area and have enormous potential 
            for carbon sequestration. Healthy soil in gardens can store substantial amounts of carbon 
            when managed sustainably through no-dig methods and organic matter addition.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            With climate change bringing wetter winters and more frequent drought periods in summer, 
            sustainable gardens help buffer these extremes by improving soil structure and water 
            retention capabilities.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Peatland Protection</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">
              Ireland's peatlands store over 1.6 billion tonnes of carbon - using peat-free compost 
              helps protect these valuable carbon sinks and unique ecosystems.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8 bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Water Quality Improvement</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Irish waterways face pollution challenges from agricultural and urban runoff. Sustainable 
          gardens act as natural filters, particularly important in a country with abundant rainfall 
          and interconnected watersheds.
        </p>
        <p>
          By eliminating chemical pesticides and fertilizers, you prevent harmful substances from 
          washing into streams, rivers, and eventually the sea. This helps protect Ireland's 
          freshwater fish, including the vulnerable Atlantic salmon and native brown trout.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Seasonal Practices Section -->
    <section id="seasonal" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 border-b pb-2">Seasonal Sustainable Gardening in Ireland</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-600">Spring (March-May)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Start seeds in recycled containers</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Use egg cartons, yogurt pots, and toilet paper rolls instead of buying plastic pots</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Prepare garden beds without digging</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Use no-dig methods to preserve soil structure and beneficial organisms</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Install rainwater harvesting system</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Prepare for summer by collecting spring showers in water butts</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Plant native pollinator-friendly flowers</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Support early-emerging bees with spring-flowering natives</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-yellow-600">Summer (June-August)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Water efficiently during dry spells</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Water deeply but less frequently, and in evenings to reduce evaporation</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Apply organic mulches</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Use grass clippings, straw or compost to retain soil moisture</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Harvest and preserve produce</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Reduce food waste by properly storing or preserving surplus harvest</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Use natural pest control methods</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Encourage ladybirds, lacewings and other beneficial insects for pest control</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-orange-600">Autumn (September-November)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Collect leaves for leaf mould</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Create valuable soil conditioner from autumn leaves</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Plant cover crops</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Protect bare soil with green manures to prevent erosion</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Save seeds from open-pollinated plants</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Preserve genetic diversity and reduce need to buy new seeds</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Create habitat piles</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Leave some plant material and create log piles for overwintering wildlife</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-600">Winter (December-February)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Plan next year's garden</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Design crop rotations and incorporate more native plants</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Maintain tools sustainably</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Clean, oil, and repair tools to extend their lifespan</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Provide wildlife resources</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Supply water, food, and shelter for garden wildlife during lean months</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-semibold">Plant bare-root trees and hedging</span>
                <p class="text-sm">Winter is ideal for establishing native trees and hedges in Ireland</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Practical Steps Section -->
    <section id="practical" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 border-b pb-2">Practical Sustainability Steps for Irish Gardeners</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="flex items-center text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary p-2 rounded-full mr-2">1</span>
            Embrace Peat-Free Gardening
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Ireland's peatlands are vital carbon sinks and unique habitats. By choosing peat-free composts 
            and soil improvers, you help protect these threatened ecosystems.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">How to start:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Look for composts labeled "peat-free" or containing wood fiber, coir, or composted green waste</li>
              <li>Make your own compost from garden and kitchen waste</li>
              <li>Use leaf mould as a peat alternative for seed starting and potting mixes</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="flex items-center text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary p-2 rounded-full mr-2">2</span>
            Support Native Biodiversity
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Ireland has a unique but threatened flora and fauna. Your garden can become a refuge 
            for native species by incorporating plants that have evolved alongside Irish wildlife.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">How to start:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Include at least 30% native plants in your garden</li>
              <li>Create wildlife corridors with native hedgerows (hawthorn, blackthorn, holly)</li>
              <li>Incorporate wildflower areas with species native to your region of Ireland</li>
              <li>Allow some "wild" areas where nature can follow its own patterns</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="flex items-center text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary p-2 rounded-full mr-2">3</span>
            Practice Natural Soil Building
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Healthy soil is the foundation of a sustainable garden. By working with natural processes, 
            you can build soil fertility without synthetic inputs.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">How to start:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Adopt no-dig or minimum-till methods to preserve soil structure</li>
              <li>Make compost from garden and kitchen waste</li>
              <li>Use green manures like phacelia, clover, or field beans to cover bare soil and add nutrients</li>
              <li>Apply organic mulches to suppress weeds and feed soil life</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="flex items-center text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary p-2 rounded-full mr-2">4</span>
            Create a Water-Wise Garden
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            While Ireland receives abundant rainfall, climate change is bringing more erratic patterns 
            with extended dry periods. Water conservation remains an essential sustainability practice.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">How to start:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Install water butts to harvest rainwater from roofs</li>
              <li>Group plants with similar water needs together</li>
              <li>Choose drought-tolerant plants for areas that receive little rainfall</li>
              <li>Use ollas (buried clay pots) or drip irrigation for efficient watering</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-base-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="flex items-center text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary p-2 rounded-full mr-2">5</span>
            Track Your Impact
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Understanding and measuring the impact of your sustainable gardening efforts helps 
            you continually improve and see the difference you're making.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">How to start:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Use our <a href="/sustainability-tracker" class="text-primary underline">Sustainability Tracker</a> to monitor your progress</li>
              <li>Keep records of harvests, wildlife sightings, and resource usage</li>
              <li>Calculate how much water you've saved through conservation practices</li>
              <li>Estimate carbon footprint reduction from growing your own food</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <div class="bg-base-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Join Our Sustainable Gardening Community</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The journey toward sustainable gardening is more enjoyable when shared with others. Connect with 
        fellow Irish gardeners who are also working to create more environmentally-friendly gardens.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/sustainability-tracker" class="btn btn-primary">Track Your Progress</a>
        <a href="/plant-recommendations" class="btn btn-outline">Get Sustainable Plant Recommendations</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
